{[#]} 6. Nh4 $1 {now we see why in many cases Black is spending a tempo on the
move h7-h6} Bg6 7. O-O {normally in this position I would consider to play
with 000, but the "problem" here is that we have already played Be2, and now
it will be harder to play with d3-Nd2 and Qe2, exactly because the e2 square
is already taken by our bishop!} Bd6 8. d3 Nbd7 9. Nd2 {In general we are not
in a big hurry to take on g6, and we will try to don't do it AT LEAST until
Black hasn't played 00, otherwise, after Nxg6-hxg6 the 'h' line could be a
problem with the rook still on h8} *

